Observations:

The src folder contains the React component files.
The public folder contains the index.html entry point.
node_modules stores external libraries.
App.js uses JSX for structure, useState() for state, and props can be passed to child components.
Hot reloading improves productivity.

Learnings:

Created a functional component with state and JSX.
Understood how the build process works.
Explored the React app structure and files.
Developed a basic understanding of the development workflow.
